    <item>
      <title>Jekyll &#43; Github &#43; Markdown = Blog</title>
      <link>http://code.markedmondson.me/hello-world/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 14 Jan 2016 23:03:57 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://code.markedmondson.me/hello-world/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;p&gt;Hello World!  Welcome to my new home for code blogging.  I&amp;rsquo;ll keep the &lt;a href=&#34;http://markedmondson.me&#34;&gt;regular blog&lt;/a&gt; for all the other stuff, running on &lt;a href=&#34;https://posthaven.com/&#34;&gt;Posthaven&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;why&#34;&gt;Why?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its educational, and free, and writing code posts using Posthaven&amp;rsquo;s rich text editor was sometimes painful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using this setup means its all written in Markdown so I get control over everything just the way I want it, and since it combines &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Github&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://help.github.com/articles/getting-started-with-writing-and-formatting-on-github/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Markdown&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, two things I know well already, &lt;a href=&#34;https://jekyllrb.com/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Jekyll&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; seemed worth knowing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I followed the guide from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/08/build-blog-jekyll-github-pages/&#34;&gt;Smashing Magazine&lt;/a&gt; which meant I was up and running in 10 minutes.  There were a few things like updating the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/barryclark/jekyll-now&#34;&gt;Jekyll-now fork&lt;/a&gt; to include the latest builds:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. I did have to edit these bits:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34;&gt;markdown: kramdown
highlighter: rouge
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip;but I guess it will catch up soon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also would ideally have liked this to appear at &lt;a href=&#34;http://markedmondson.me/code/hello-world&#34;&gt;http://markedmondson.me/code/hello-world&lt;/a&gt; but couldn&amp;rsquo;t figure out how.  Who cares about SEO anyhow. ;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-to-expect&#34;&gt;What to expect&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ll be hopefully putting my R package updates, Google Analytcs / Google Tag Manager guides, R data analytics and general digital analytics stuff here.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
